definition.value: An amino disaccharide consisting of an alpha-D-glucopyranose residue and a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
An amino trisaccharide comprising beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3) and (1->6).
A glycosylglycerol that is 1-O-(beta-D-glucosyl)glycerol in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the glucose ring has been converted to the corresponding beta-D-galactopyranoside.
A alpha-D-Galp-(1->4)-D-Glcp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
A glycosylmannose consisting of alpha-D-galactopyranose and D-mannopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
